    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allInvoiceLineMaps" id="028d1325-d741-4320-8934-7606405126a4">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CM_InvoiceLineDescMapDict"/>
        <text>###################################
###################################
#### TFS 40620 DO NOT USE THIS COLLECTION  ###
###################################
###################################


Each individual invoice line mapping, with individual method values.  Since CCMS QNS 2177 replaced by CM_TranMapInvoiceLineMapping 
  entries in allTMInvoiceLineMappings.  At some point this should be removed as now duplicated and all usage replaced with allTMInvoiceLineMappings.</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allInvoiceLinesUsed" id="8308feec-7816-4e5b-a266-4d902b4fc46f">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CM_InvoiceLineDescByNarrDict"/>
        <text>###################################
###################################
#### TFS 40620 DO NOT USE THIS COLLECTION  ###
###################################
###################################

Each unique CM_InvoiceLineDesc in both allInvoiceLineMaps and allTMInvoiceLineMappings.
This collection is used to show the unique invoice line types in the transaction map whereas allTMInvoiceLineMappings 
  is used to maintain the invoice line types, with the additional method maps and grouping.
The allInvoiceLineMaps and allTMInvoiceLineMappings collections can have the same invoice line type in multiple times
  for a different set of map methods and/or groupings, where this allInvoiceLinesUsed will have the invoice line type only once
  so could be a smaller collection.</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allRegisteredMethods" id="b32d3fbf-5eee-43f4-94fa-9aa48f0c92af">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="StringArray"/>
        <text>The mapping of invoice lines corresponds to 'is' methods on the cargo e.g. isOD, is40 etc.

If no 'is' options are selected in the UI mapping then this collection is empty.

If there are methods in this collection, each will be asked of the cargo the answer is user as a bit in the byte stored in an integer called mapValue.

The name of the internal method corresponding to each question in the Invoice Line Mapping screen that has been selected.

All the invoice line mappings are stored in CM_TranMapInvoiceLineMapping, these are in allTMInvoiceLineMappings keyed by the mapValue.
The mapValue is used as the external key for the collection of CM_TranMapInvoiceLineMapping.</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="allTMInvoiceLineMappings" id="1e15d12c-9fbe-4f32-951b-f8ef7d4ace80">
        <kind>parent</kind>
        <transientToPersistentAllowed/>
        <updateMode>automatic</updateMode>
        <type name="CM_TMInvLineMapByCargoAttrDict"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Each individual invoice line mapping, with individual method values added for CCMS QNS 2177 using CM_TranMapInvoiceLineMapping
  to hold additional new detail of the CM_TranMapInvoiceLineGroupType value.  Makes the original allInvoiceLineMaps no longer necessary
  but both are maintained so far.
This should be the only collection used when reading the transaction map for charging.</text>
        <Inverse name="CM_TranMapInvoiceLineMapping::myQuantityRangeMap"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
