    <PrimAttribute name="rangeType" id="b57d9033-1bf5-4982-9662-5897acc13281">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Added for free storage days but not used in the end.  Values are RANGETYPE_DEFAULT and RANGETYPE_FSD_RELATIVE (not used).
The original intent was to be able to specify storage day ranges as relative to the number of days of free storage, 
 something like 0 - FSD, FSD+1 to FSD+10, FSD+11 to FSD+20 and so on, but this all got too hard and not actually needed/useful at this point (late 2012).</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <JadeMethod name="addMethod" id="a6aa22b6-2e86-458e-9d0a-12092e071b15">
        <updating/>
        <source>addMethod(_methodName : String) updating;
// 34477 from transaction map load
vars

begin
	if not self.allRegisteredMethods.includes(_methodName) then
		self.allRegisteredMethods.add(_methodName);
	endif;

end;
</source>
        <Parameter name="_methodName" type="String"/>
    </JadeMethod>
